'''ENSA – Seguros de Angola S.A.''' is the main [[insurance company]] in [[Angola]]. It was created in 1978 as Empresa Nacional de Seguros e Resseguros de Angola as (U.E.E.; Unidade Economica Estatal), but was later converted into a [[joint-stock company]].<ref name="ENSA_ensa">{{Cite web |url=http://www.ensa.co.ao/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=48&Itemid=74|title=A ENSA |accessdate=27 March 2012}}</ref>

ENSA is a [[holding company]] managing two operating companies: ENSA S.A., an [[insurance]] company, and ENSA RE SA, a [[reinsurance]] company. ENSA also has holdings in a number of other industries. The firm employs 700 people, 40% of them female. ENSA works through 30 [[branch office]]s of its own, and sells its services at 54 post offices and one bank. ENSA's [[call center]] can deal with 1,000 clients in one 8-hour work shift. ENSA claims to hold more than 50% of the Angolan insurance market.<ref name="ENSA_numeros">{{Cite web|url=http://www.ensa.co.ao/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=82&Itemid=75 |title=NÚMEROS ENSA |accessdate=27 March 2012 }}</ref>

