The '''Embassy of [[Norway]] in Dublin''', officially the '''Royal Norwegian Embassy''', was established in 1983. The mission of the Embassy is to promote Norwegian interests in the [[Republic of Ireland]] and to improve further the [[Foreign relations of the Republic of Ireland|Norwegian-Irish relations]]. The Embassy works in close co-operation with Irish and Norwegian public and private institutions, as well as with organisations and individuals.<ref>[https://www.norway.no/en/ireland/norway/about-embassy/ About the embassy] (Embassy website)</ref>

The Embassy does not handle visa applications.

