'''Mamer communal council''' ({{lang-fr|Conseil communal de Mamer}}) is the [[Local government|local council]] for the [[Communes of Luxembourg|commune]] of [[Mamer]], in south-western [[Luxembourg]].
It consists of thirteen members, elected every six years by [[proportional representation]].<ref name="Conseil communal">{{cite web |url=http://www.mamer.lu/index.php?page=4.30&filter=&what= |title=Le Conseil communal |accessdate=2007-09-16 |date= |publisher=Commune of Mamer |language=fr}}</ref> The last elections were held on 9 October 2005, and resulted in a victory for the [[Christian Social People's Party]] (CSV). In the ''[[Collège échevinal (Luxembourg)|collège échevinal]]'', the CSV forms a coalition with [[Luxembourg Socialist Workers' Party]] (LSAP), who have the second-largest contingent, under the leadership of CSV [[Mayor of Mamer|mayor]] [[Gilles Roth]].<ref name="Conseil communal" />
