[[File:Wagon luxe sitarail.jpg|thumb|right|250px|A [[Sitarail]] train]] [[File:Gare sitarail Agbovile.JPG|thumb|right|250px|[[Agboville]] station]] [[Ivory Coast]] (Côte d'Ivoire) has 660 kilometres of railway (1995 estimate). The [[track gauge]] is {{RailGauge|1000mm}}.
This railway was built during the French colonial period, and links the port city of [[Abidjan]] with [[Ouagadougou]], the capital of [[Burkina Faso]].
In October 2010, the government announced plans to build a 737&nbsp;km line which would link the port of [[San Pédro, Côte d'Ivoire|San Pedro]] to mines in the west of the country.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-05/ivory-coast-plans-to-build-railway-to-boost-output-from-its-western-mines.html |accessdate=2010-10-06 |title=Ivory Coast to Build Railway to Boost Output From Western Mines - Bloomberg }}</ref>
